
---

#gitignore

Since you're using Java + Node + Docker, here is a combined `.gitignore`:

```gitignore
# ======================
# Java / Maven / Gradle
# ======================
target/
build/
.gradle/
*.class
*.log

# IntelliJ
.idea/
*.iml

# Eclipse
.project
.classpath
.settings/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# ======================
# Node.js
# ======================
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Playwright
playwright-report/
test-results/

# ======================
# Logs
# ======================
logs/
*.log

# ======================
# OS Files
# ======================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ======================
# Docker
# ======================
*.tar

# ======================
# Environment Files
# ======================
.env
.env.local

# ======================
# Temporary Files
# ======================
*.tmp
*.swp
